title: Kara Swisher on Zuckerberg's meeting with Pres. Trump, Ellison's Uber slam
text: Kara Swisher, editor-at-large at Recode, joins CNBC's "Closing Bell" to discuss Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg's meeting with President Donald Trump, Larry Ellison's harsh words for Uber and more.

title: Few U.S. lawmakers hit 'like' button after Facebook CEO visits Capitol Hill
text: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg wrapped up three days of discussions with Washington movers and shakers on Friday, with few if any indications he had won new “friends” to help the top social media company deal with multiple probes by Congress, state attorneys general and federal regulators.

title: Facebook suspends thousands of apps over privacy issues

title: Facebook fundraising tools have raised more than $2 billion
text: Facebook Inc. FB, -0.11% users have raised more than $2 billion for charitable causes since the social-media company made it possible on its platform in 2015, the company said.

title: Facebook has suspended tens of thousands of apps after Cambridge Analytica investigation
text: Since the Cambridge Analytica scandal in March 2018, Facebook has suspended tens of thousands of apps stemming from an investigation into its developer ecosystem.

title: Facebook has suspended ‘tens of thousands’ of apps suspected of hoarding data
text: Facebook has suspended “tens of thousands” of apps connected to its platform which it suspects may be collecting large amounts of user profile data. title: Facebook suspends tens of thousands of apps following Cambridge Analytica scandal
text: The suspended apps were tied to 400 developers.

title: Facebook suspends tens of thousands of apps in response to Cambridge Analytica row
text: Facebook Inc  said on Friday it has suspended tens of thousands of apps on the social networking platform, as part of the company's ongoing app developer investigation it began in March 2018 in response to the Cambridge Analytica row.

title: Facebook's Zuckerberg pledges cooperation with U.S. antitrust probe: congressman
text: Congressman David Cicilline, chair of the U.S. House Judiciary Committee's antitrust panel, said on Friday that Facebook Chief Executive Mark Zuckerberg pledged cooperation with the panel's probe into online markets during a meeting on Capitol Hill.

title: Facebook Says It Has Suspended ‘Tens of Thousands’ of Apps

title: Undeterred, Facebook to press on with Libra launch next year: executive
text: Facebook still aims to launch its Libra digital currency next year, its executive overseeing the project told Swiss newspaper NZZ, as the company presses ahead despite authorities around the world pouring cold water on the plans.

title: Widespread climate walkouts expected at Amazon, Microsoft, Google, Facebook and many other tech companies
text: Climate change will take center stage in the technology industry today as thousands of employees at some of the world’s biggest and most influential companies plan to walk off the job.

title: President Trump says his meeting with Mark Zuckerberg 'constructive'
text: Mark Zuckerberg met with President Trump and a number of other lawmakers in D.C. with the president tweeting a photo of the face-to-face meeting, saying it was "constructive."
